The checkout optimization effort, tracked under issue V2-5265, focused on significantly reducing the redirection time
  from the preview page to the checkout page, which was identified as approximately 30 seconds. The strategy involves
  implementing asynchronous handling for key "fire and forget" APIs: create_preview_analytics, update_preview_analytics,
  register, and create_order.

  A detailed test plan, including specific test cases and documentation, has been created to verify the baseline
  performance, confirm the optimized redirection time (targeting under 5 seconds), validate the asynchronous nature of
  the APIs, ensure graceful error handling, and maintain the integrity of the entire user journey. The evidence
  directory contains video recordings, presumably to document test execution. The current status indicates that test
  execution is pending, with the final report template ready to be filled upon completion of the tests.
